### Post-Stage 2 Polish (2026-03-28)

**Bug fixes:**
- Ghost node bug: `onSave` firing on blur after discard was writing empty nodes to DB. Fixed with `discardedRef` ‚Äî a Set that marks node IDs as discarded before any save can fire
- Popover re-opening bug: `setSelectedNode(saved)` after temp node save re-opened popover. Changed to `setSelectedNode(null)`
- Double node creation on blur: clicking away fired both `onSave` (blur) and `onNodeCreate` (canvas click). Fixed by setting `suppressNextCreateRef.current = true` at top of `onSave`

**Keyboard shortcuts:**
- `Enter` ‚Äî saves and closes
- `Escape` ‚Äî discards if empty, closes
- `Tab` on empty node ‚Äî moves node right by `tabIndentX`
- `Shift+Tab` ‚Äî moves node left by `tabIndentX`
- `Tab` on filled node ‚Äî saves current node, creates child at `(x + tabIndentX, calcDynamicY(text))` with explicit edge
- `Shift+Enter` ‚Äî saves current node, creates new node below at `(x, calcDynamicY(text))` with explicit edge
- `Shift+Arrow` ‚Äî repositions current node in arrow direction using `tabIndentX` (left/right) and `shiftEnterIndentY` (up/down); works on empty or filled nodes; does not save or create
- `Delete`/`Backspace` ‚Äî deletes all selected nodes when selection active and no textarea focused
- Tab/Shift+Enter await `onSave` before calling `onNodeCreateFromEdge` so real node ID is used as edge source
- `onSave` returns `Promise<string>` (real node ID after DB write)

**Other:**
- "Select subtree" button in popover triggers BFS subtree selection
- Delete button in popover with immediate confirm
- `calcDynamicY(text)` ‚Äî computes child Y as `node.y + Math.ceil(text.length / wrapLength) * defaultSize + shiftEnterIndentY`


### Image Nodes (2026-04-09)
- `src/lib/isImageUrl.ts` ‚Äî detects image URLs by extension or known host (imgur, unsplash, wikimedia)
- `Canvas.tsx` `allNodes.each` block: if node text is an image URL, loads via `window.Image()` to get natural dimensions, appends `<clipPath>` + `<image>` at native size with `xMidYMid meet` and rounded corners; early-returns if `<image>` already present to prevent flicker on drag. Else falls through to existing tspan text rendering.

